                  "severity": "High",
                  "type": "Tampering",
                  "description": "A user can modify frontend-generated API requests before they reach the backend, including values such as userId, role, price or object identifiers.",
                  "mitigation": "Apply a zero-trust approach to all frontend input. Treat every request field as attacker-controlled. Enforce authentication, authorisation, input validation, ownership checks, and business rules on the backend. Return only the data required for the authenticated user and requested operation.",
