                  "title": "Injection in Database Query",
                  "status": "Open",
                  "severity": "High",
                  "type": "Tampering",
                  "description": "User-controlled input may be included in database queries without safe parameterisation or strict query construction. This could allow an attacker to alter query logic, access unauthorised data, modify records, bypass authentication, or trigger database errors.\n",
                  "mitigation": "Use parameterised queries or prepared statements. For NoSQL databases, enforce strict input types and schemas, reject operator-shaped input, and avoid passing user-controlled objects directly into query filters. Apply least-privilege permissions to the database account.",
